                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/147.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister to Honduras</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-12T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department learns that revolutionary activities are at present in progress in
                    Guatemala under Generals Prudencio Alfaro and Lino A. Barahona, and that
                    President Bonilla is cooperating with the President of Guatemala. Immediately
                    bring this to the attention of the Government of Honduras and urge strict
                    observance of the Washington conventions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
